Title: Low-Temperature Thermodynamics of $A^{(2)}_2$ and su(3)-invariant Spin

ChainsAuthors: Luca Mezincescu, Rafael I. Nepomechie, P. K. Townsend, and A. M.

TsvelikComments: 31 pages, UMTG-169

Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B406 (1993) 681-707

We formulate the thermodynamic Bethe Ansatz (TBA) equations for the closed(periodic boundary conditions) $A^{(2)}_2$ quantum spin chain in an externalmagnetic field, in the (noncritical) regime where the anisotropy parameter$\eta$ is real. In the limit $\eta \to 0$, we recover the TBA equations of theantiferromagnetic su(3)-invariant chain in the fundamental representation. Wesolve these equations for low temperature and small field, and calculate thespecific heat and magnetic susceptibility.